    • setState

      public boolean setState​(boolean state, int ID, java.lang.String user)
      Parameters:
      state - if the book is taken or not
      ID - if book is being taken, then method gets taker's ID, if it is being returned, method gets -1
      user - string to determine if it is a librarian or a reader. Gets null if book is being returned to keep the last user's info
      Returns:
      true if everything is okay, false if user != null and String user is not equal to InterfaceStrings.librarian or InterfaceStrings.reader (but that shouldn't happen)
